the site of aesthetics, against the colonization of time. Analyzing the work of artists and revolutionaries like ADÁL, Lebrón, Papo Colo, Pedro Pietri, and Ryan Rivera, Ricanness imagines a Rican future through the time travel extended in their aesthetic interventions, illustrating how they have reformulated time itself through nonlinear aesthetic practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aArts, Puerto RicanxThemes, motives. 0aArts, Puerto Rican-Themes, motives. 0aGroup identity in art. 0aPostcolonialism and the artszPuerto Rico. 0aPostcolonialism and the arts-Puerto Rico. 0aTime and artzPuerto Rico. 0aTime and art-Puerto Rico. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Hispanic American Studies.2bisacsh  aADÁL.  aBrownness.  aDa-sein.  aEl Museo del Barrio.  aFrantz Fanon.  aGuy Debord.  aHurricane Maria.  aLolita Lebrón.  aMartin Heidegger.  aNietzsche.  aPapo Colo.  aPedro Pietri.  aPuerto Rican Nationalist Party.  aPuerto Rican.  aabsurdism.  aaesthetics.  acolonialism.  acrisis.  adeath drive.  adrama.  adreaming.  aduration.  aemergency.  aendurance.  aexistentialism.  aexperimental.  afutural.  aimagination.  alooping.  anonlinear time.  aperformance art.  aphilosophy.  apoetry.  apostcolonial.  apoverty.  aqueer.  aracialized masculinity.  arape.  aslow death.  atheater.  aunwantedness.  avideo art.  aviolence.  avulgarity.40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479888740.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479890705423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479890705/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles